name: Rochester Coffee Corner - WiC Hacks Project
description:
This is a website I designed for the Women in Computing hackathon at the Rochester Institute of Technology in March 2022.


The project aims to be a central location to feature all of the coffee shops in the downtown Rochester area. The goal is to feature all of the products the locations offer in one place, as well as provide the consumers about information about the origin of the products. The website also offers a "Recipes" section where users are able to select which products they have at home and be provided with recipes they can make.
